WEBVTT

00:03:29.392 --> 00:03:32.819
As a citizen."

00:03:32.819 --> 00:03:34.415
Now, this is the way Aaron was.

00:03:34.415 --> 00:03:39.476
He didn't tell. He asked questions.

00:03:39.476 --> 00:03:41.226
But his questions spoke as clearly

00:03:41.226 --> 00:03:43.914
as my four-year-old's hug.

00:03:43.914 --> 00:03:45.330
He was saying to me,

00:03:45.330 --> 00:03:47.262
"You've got to get a clue.

00:03:47.262 --> 00:03:48.938
You have got to get a clue, because there is

00:03:48.938 --> 00:03:52.000
a flaw at the core of the operating system

00:03:52.000 --> 00:03:53.507
of this democracy,

00:03:53.507 --> 00:03:57.805
and it's not a flaw every one out of 360 billion times

00:03:57.805 --> 00:03:59.597
our democracy tries to make a decision.

00:03:59.597 --> 00:04:01.418
It is every time,